Currently there are three translations of the [[Bible]] into modern [[Kyrgyz language|Kyrgyz]].
Ray of Hope (Боорукерликтин өкүлдүгү «ҮМҮТ НУРУ») produced a translation from the [[Russian Synodal Bible|Russian Synodal Version]]. This is the most commonly used translation.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}
Lingua Service («Лингвосервис» борбору) together with the United Bible Society (Бириккен Ыйык Китеп Коомдору) published a new translation of the [[New Testament]] in 2005. They are currently working on the Old Testament.
Askar Mambetaliev has translated a large portion of the Bible into a more dynamic equivalent/paraphrase translation.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}} This translation is specially intended for [[evangelism]].{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}
[[Jehovah's Witnesses]] have revised the Ray of Hope translation to match closer to the English [[New World Translation]] producing a Kyrgyz "New World Translation", ''Жаңы дүйнө котормосу''.{{fact|date=February 2018}}
