'''Burkina Sign Language''' (in French: ''Langue des signes mossi'') is the indigenous [[sign language]] of the [[Deaf community]] in the capital of Burkina Faso, [[Ouagadougou]]. Deaf education in Burkina is in [[American Sign Language]].<ref>{{cite book|first=Diane|last=Brentari |title=Sign Languages |year=2010 |publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|page=406|isbn=1139487396}}</ref> There are 55,500 deaf people in Burkina<ref>International Mission Board.(2017). People groups. http://www.peoplegroups.org/explore/groupdetails.aspx?peid=47719</ref>
