{{Infobox language |name=Cakfem-Mushere |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Plateau State]] |speakers=5,000 |date=1990 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[West Chadic languages|West Chadic]] |fam4=[[Bole–Angas languages|Bole–Angas]] |fam5=[[Angas languages|Angas]] (A.3) |iso3=cky |glotto=cakf1236 |glottorefname=Cakfem-Mushere }}
'''Cakfem-Mushere''' is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language cluster spoken in [[Plateau State]], [[Nigeria]]. Dialects are Kadim-Kaban and Jajura.<ref name=e18/> [[Mutual intelligibility]] with [[Mwaghavul language|Mwaghavul]] is high.<ref name="Blench2017">Blench, Roger. 2017. [https://www.academia.edu/35507157/CURRENT_RESEARCH_ON_THE_A3_WEST_CHADIC_LANGUAGES Current research on the A3 West Chadic languages].</ref>
'''Mushere''' is very close to [[Mwaghavul language|Mwaghavul]].<ref name="Blench2017"/>
'''Cakfem''' has two varieties, namely '''Outer Cakfem''' and '''Inner Cakfem'''. Outer Cakfem is very similar to [[Mwaghavul language|Mwaghavul]], but Inner Cakfem is more divergent, as [[Mwaghavul language|Mwaghavul]] speakers have trouble understanding Inner Cakfem.<ref name="Blench2017"/>
