{{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Diwakar Krushna Kelkar | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = दिवाकर कृष्ण केळकर | native_name_lang = deva | pseudonym = Diwakar Krushna | birth_name = | birth_date = 1902 | birth_place = Maharashtra, India | death_date = {{death year and age|1973|1902}} | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = Writer | language = | nationality = | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = Samadhiwarali Phule, Rupagarvita Ani Itar Goshti | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
{{Unreferenced|date=August 2009}} '''Diwakar Krushna Kelkar''' ([[Devanagari]]: दिवाकर कृष्ण केळकर) (1902 – 1973) was a [[Marathi people|Marathi]] writer from [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]. He wrote short stories, plays, and novels under the name '''Diwakar Krushna''' (दिवाकर कृष्ण).
He worked as a lawyer in the city of [[Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh|Hyderabad]], which is now in [[Andhra Pradesh]].
Kelkar was a pioneer in composing Marathi short stories which brought out the inner workings of the human mind.{{Citation needed|date=October 2009}}
''Samadhiwarali Phule'' (समाधीवरली फुले) and ''Rupagarvita Ani Itar Goshti'' (रूपगर्विता आणि इतर गोष्टी) are two compilations of his short stories.
