'''Riyaz''' (also '''Riyaaz''') is a [[Hindustani language|Hindustani]] term used for [[music practice]], for honing of [[Hindustani classical music]] vocal as well as instrument skills in the [[Indian subcontinent]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Art school: (propositions for the 21st century)|publisher=MIT Press|year=2009|isbn=0-262-13493-4 |page=76 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0X6TL22DrMsC&pg=PA76&dq=Riyaaz&hl=en&sa=X&ei=J4gRT8yAEsLWrQfA1Mz9AQ&ved=0CEcQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=Riyaaz&f=false |ref= }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Theory and practice of tabla|author= Sadanand Naimpalli|publisher=Popular Prakashan|year=2005|isbn=81-7991-149-7 | page = 51 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QOSXX270RxMC&pg=PA51&dq=Riyaaz&hl=en&sa=X&ei=J4gRT8yAEsLWrQfA1Mz9AQ&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Riyaaz&f=false |ref= }}</ref> It is known as '''Sadhakam''' or '''Sadhana''' in [[Carnatic music]].<ref>{{cite news |title= The Riyaz Shows|author= |url= http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/06/27/stories/2008062751220200.htm|newspaper= The Hindu|date= |accessdate=16 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title= Talas of Virtuosity|author= |url= http://www.thehindu.com/arts/music/article2758156.ece|newspaper= The Hindu|date= |accessdate=16 January 2012}}</ref> It is followed rigorously by the students as well as exponents of vocal as well as dancing forms.
==The practice== The ''Riyaaz'' or ''Sadhakam'', which often starts early in the morning at four,<ref>{{cite news |title= Bonding with the Gurus|author= |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/07/04/stories/2008070451360300.htm |newspaper= The Hindu|date= |accessdate=16 January 2012}}</ref> is taken seriously by the students for it requires intensity, discipline and commitment for years and forms an important component in the ''Guru - Shishya parampara'' (teacher-student tradition).<ref>{{cite news |title= Music is the only Constant in my life:Asha Bhosle|author= |url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/music-is-the-only-constant-in-my-life-asha/520017/|newspaper= Indian Express|date= |accessdate=16 January 2012}}</ref>
In Carnatic music, the impression is that the assiduous sadhakam of the [[Trinity of Carnatic Music]] was the bedrock of the excellence of the old-world vidwans.<ref>{{cite news |title= Bakti and sadhaka - Pillars of Excellence|author= |url= http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/ms/2001/12/01/stories/2001120100020100.htm|newspaper= The Hindu|date= |accessdate=16 January 2012}}</ref>
